Caption:
I’ve been a little quiet here lately- the truth is I’ve been deep in development of a new curriculum for @antiochseattle called “The Thriving Artist- (sell your art, not your soul).” 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This 10 week course is the synthesis of everything I’ve learned in the 15+ years of doing art professionally. We talk money, presentation, websites, galleries and so much more.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is the course I wish I could have taken when I was just starting out, and I’m SO EXCITED to share it with my students starting next week. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Right now it’s only available through Antioch University, but guess what? I’ll be releasing it to the public as an online option later this year! (Omg. Cats out the bag. 🐈 )
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Now is the time for us all to step into our creative power and gifts, as I truly believe artists can change the world.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A big part of that ⬆️ is figuring out how to make money doing this. That’s what I want to help you with. I’ll be talking more about the upcoming course here on IG in the next few months, but the best way to make sure you don’t miss registration?
⬇️⬇️⬇️
Sign up for my email list (link in bio). 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’ll send you some nice freebies right away and then leave you alone until I’ve got something time sensitive to share.😂
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Stay tuned!
Xo

Caption:
‘Today with Me’, mural inspired by, and symbolic of Christ’s crucifixion. 
🌲
The Kauri trees represent the crosses that Jesus and the two criminals were crucified upon. Kauri chosen for their tall, straight structure and to relate this event in a way unique to the native flora of Aotearoa.
🐑
The title comes from the conversation between the ‘believing’ criminal and Jesus response to him that ‘today you will be with me in paradise’. 
🌳
There are other symbols interwoven in this allegorical artwork, and I hope meaning that will become apparent to many viewers over time. 
❤️
I feel very privileged to have been given the opportunity to paint on this wall, grateful to the three wonderful women that worked alongside to complete the painting... and also a sense of achievement that I didn’t freak out being up such a tall ladder!!
🌺
I hope you all have a safe, reflective and restful Easter. Xx

Caption:
It didn't take long after I started my street art project that I began getting push back from people. A few upset messages that I was going against the stay at home orders (true) and by putting art out, I was encouraging people to do the same (debatable) and thus putting people in danger (I could not disagree more.) Just irritated that I had the nerve to be creating art during a pandemic. Arguably, I felt art is what we could all use more of. It was the first time that I had gotten negative feedback like that for my art, and it immediately signaled to me that I was doing something important, and that I should ABSOLUTELY keep doing it. Thankfully the positive messages far outweighed the negative, but unfortunately those negative ones are the ones that you spend more energy on. 

On one particular day I got a slew of awful messages from a young man who was losing his mind that I was doing street art. He was irate I had used the hashtag #graffiti and berated me, my art, and my character over the course of several hours. It was amusing to say the least. I even offered to meet him for coffee- my treat. Surprise, surprise... he declined the offer. But in that fiery exchange of hate messages, he said I was a disgrace to the graffiti and street art community and my stuff was yuppie eyesore garbage. I didn't waste a second before heading into my studio to paint this one as a tribute to one of my first haters, and I've used the hashtag #yuppieeyesoregarbage ever since. 

Don't let the jerkwads get you down. If anything, let them inspire you. They're just as important to the journey as the people who cheer you on. And for that, I have immense gratitude. 🙏❤
.
.

Caption:
Vita e Morte – Herbert Baglione  

Via delle Conce, 13 - Roma, Italia
Latitude: 41.874080 | Longitude: 12.478001 

Lo so, lo so… lo scorso venerdì ho saltato un appuntamento della rubrica #streetartdenoantri.

 Sono settimane molto intense con tanti nuovi progetti personali e lavorativi che piano piano stanno prendendo forma e questo ahimè mi porta ad avere meno tempo libero.  

Ma per farmi perdonare torno oggi con un’opera davvero incredibile! Siamo ancora una volta al quartiere Ostiense, all’ombra della Piramide Cestia e il nome dell’opera è “Vita e Morte” dello street artist brasiliano Herbert Baglione. 

Siamo sul muro esterno della storica falegnameria Blasi e con questo murales l’artista  rappresenta figure umane distorte che evocano l’immagine di un mondo alienato da sé, distratto e confuso.  

Il significato dell’opera è una critica alla società contemporanea. I personaggi, infatti, si trovano in un mare scuro e denso in cui galleggiano da soli e lontani gli uni dagli altri. L'artista usa questa metafora per dirci che nella società in cui viviamo siamo tutti quanti individui isolati e distratti, spesso sovrastati da una nube di pensieri grigi.   

Se pubblichi foto di murales presenti a Roma usa l’hashtag #streetartdenoantri e sarò felice di ricondividerti nelle mie storie!

Caption: Olive tree leaf inspired mural with the silver leaf applied. This mural is super close to my heart. It was done in South Africa for my sister in law's (@drdebbienorval) clinic. Olive trees symbolize healing, wisdom and peace and are a representation of her amazing work to restore youth, beauty and confidence for her patients. For this mural, I started with a series of blue glazed washes in the background and then overlaid the olive leaf design on top. It's all hand painted with added distressed silver leaf to really give it dimension and shine. I was SO honored to create a mural for her clinic as a representation of her business and work.

Caption:
Eunírico, 2021 por Farmer Teut

No que diz respeito aos sonhos, longe da realidade podemos ser muitas coisas. 

O Onirismo nada mais é do que o estado mental difuso, cheio de alucinações visuais de interação entre o real e o irreal, mesmo estando acordado.

De acordo com o artista, o obra é "a representação da auto-reflexão  e construção de imagem enquanto ser humano. Uma busca interna pelo entendimento de quem sou, o que busco e qual o meu propósito."

E aí, quem é você no onírico?

Arrasta pro lado para conferir a obra completa e, para mais informações, é só clicar no link em nossa bio. Lá você pode acessar o catálogo ou chamar em nosso WhatsApp. Entre em contato e conheça mais obras de @farmer_teut

For project "Brave Wall" to celebrate the #InternationalWomensDay, in memoriam to Marielle Franco, who was a Brazilian politician, sociologist, feminist, socialist, and women rights activist.

Caption:
CAPITULO 17 MAS VALE EL ALMA QUE EL CUERPO
Antes que se descubra América, los reyes católicos idearon un siniestro sistema recaudatorio mediante el Santo Oficio (La Inquisicion).
La religión sería una excusa para perseguir y confiscar legalmente.
Los judíos fueron la primer gallina de los huevos de oro de España, quienes gracias al trabajo, podían prestar dinero a los demás, o ser prestigiosos en sus profesiones, etc..
Duro muy poco el pedirles plata por las buenas, a Elezar, Abraham y Moises, para luego convertir a la península en una brutal caza judía.
Antes que existiera Facebook, en el siglo XV, los judíos y conversos caian por la cara o por la entrega de católicos animados desde misa y púlpitos de curas que veían en cada judío muerto o expulsado, una propiedad a confiscar.
En ese contexto, los peleones salieron a quemar juderías y querer vengar a quienes habían crucificado a Cristo.
Imaginen a un español peleando porque si, peleando por plata es un asesino a sueldo...
Expulsados los judíos en 1492, la cacería siguió contra  herejes, blasfemos, sodomitas y todo aquel que pudiese afectar el poder real.
Innumerables familias y clérigos vivieron del negocio de la Santa Inquisicion, al estilo narcos.
La iglesia impuso esta franquicia en donde pisase, en España duró más que en todos lados, hasta mediados del siglo XIX y con nostálgicos en el XX y hoy.
Persecuciones, torturas y hogueras era el negocio mas lucrativo para la Corona, bajo la dirección, utilización e impulso de la Iglesia, su santa socia.
Las sospechas, delaciones y calumnias, ya no abandonarían más a los peleones, envenenando a España.
Foto del cruceiro verde de la ciudad de Betanzos (Galicia), cercano a la judería. 
Hoy, viernes santo, recordar a Cristo crucificado por nada y todo el mal que se hizo (y se hace) en su nombre, ratifica  que la mejor religión es un buen corazón.
Felices pascuas para todos.

Caption:
" Fonte de Bênçãos "

Mural que fiz na comunidade  da Mauro no bairro da Saúde  na zona sul  de São Paulo convidado pelo meu amigo Jota Bandeira.

Já se passaram  quase 23 anos pintandos na ruas de diversas cidades  e regiões, e cada vez mais tenho uma certeza.
 
 A arte é  uma poderosa ferramenta  de transformação e  transmutação de energias. Alegrando  vezes com sutileza, vezes escancaradamente a realidade de todos que vivem ao entorno e por  ali passam.

Sentir toda a receptividade, alegria e gratidão  de todas as pessoas por onde  deixo minha arte é algo realmente  verdadeiro  e gratificante. 

Agradeço  a todos artistas que contribuem  dia a dia colorindo a vidas das pessoas. Passando mensagens  de paz e questionando nossas realidades  dia a dia.

Caption:
[GRAFITE] O grafiteiro Cranio (Fabio de Oliveira Parnaiba) espalha sua arte pelos muros desde 1998. Hoje em dia, suas obras podem ser vistas não somente em São Paulo, mas em várias cidades mundo afora. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Sua marca registrada é a figura de um indígena azul, que aparece em meio à cacofonia das ruas e avenidas. O artista se vale desse personagem para intervir criticamente em temas contemporâneos como identidade, meio ambiente, violência, corrupção política e consumismo. Seus grafites contrariam a narrativa colonialista que recusa a cultura e as tradições dos povos nativos e que apresenta o indígena como alguém isolado do restante da sociedade. A arte de Cranio subverte esses valores ao escolher para protagonista um grupo social historicamente excluído.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Pichador na adolescência, Cranio mudou de rumo mais tarde. Sobre a diferença entre picho e grafite, explica: “O grafite é uma forma de linguagem mais elaborada. É feita, na maioria das vezes, durante o dia e com autorização”. A maior referência do artista é a zona norte paulistana, onde cresceu. Essa parte da cidade tem destaque na história do grafite por ser um dos primeiros lugares onde a arte urbana apareceu com força, e ainda hoje se mantém viva.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
👉 Fonte das imagens: @cranioartes 
📚 Sugestão de leitura: Maurília Gomes, José Carvalheiro. “Graffiti e crítica social: uma análise discursiva da figura do ‘índio’ na arte de Cranio”. Disponível em: 
http://ojs.labcom-ifp.ubi.pt/index.php/eikon/article/view/692

Caption:
In this life on the road, it's not a matter of if you break down, it's when you break down...We all break down, that's LIFE!!!! Some unfortunately like myself  that own a 500 dollar vehicle that btw I LOVE😂 much more frequently then others, but I'm learning it's all about your response and how you handle it.... Yes, you may lose a day of plans and for many experiences you may lose a week or more, however plans can change. Missed opportunities are the worst but each missed opportunity tends to lead to a  new one and sometimes a better one. Be open to the journey and be grateful you still have this moment at all, even with a break down, you still have air in your lungs and get to see another sunset, and maybe even another sunrise. 

And many of us, like me might even be blessed enough to know and have a great friend @electric_e046 willing enough to diagnose the issue and walk you through it. I'm so grateful for every breakdown, bc it's teaching me patience and growing my skill set. Do I want to breakdown regularly? Heck NO!! Of course NOT! But I'm not going to be negative bc it can be fixed and I WILL learn to do the job the next time it happens ❤️

Quote of the day, "Problems are not stop 🛑 signs, they are guidelines."
______________________________

Caption:
On our way to Kansas, we stayed overnight in Ft. Smith. I've never visited this small town in Western Arkansas before, had so had some exploring to do before departing.
Unfortunately, the city like so many other small cities in the United States has economic challenges. It appeared that one out of every four buildings in downtown were vacant. 
However officials are making the best of it by spicing up city center with vibrant murals and a very cute little hop on/hop off streetcar shown in these photos. These were delightful surprises to behold. There is also an art gallery and music pub in town.

Caption:
[wip] Rénovation de peintures décoratives naturalistes sur les boiseries d’un salon du XVIIIe siècle.
.
Les décorations à l’origine ont quasiment disparu avec le temps, quelques touches de peintures suggéraient des formes et volutes qui m’ont servi de base de travail.
.
Première étape d’un long projet qui s’étalera sur l’année. Une bonne phase de recherches a été nécessaire pour s’approcher de l’esprit de l’époque et ensuite me permettre repartir de zéro pour les remettre à neuf.
.
Ici je ne fais que les panneaux décoratifs, le client a le courage de s’occuper lui même du reste des boiseries ! 💪
.

Caption:
AUSBLICK 2022!
 
Im nächsten Jahr entsteht auf dem Gelände rund um die Völklinger Hütte in Zusammenarbeit mit der @StadtVölklingen und der @SaarstahlAG ein neues großformatiges Wandgemälde des Streetart-Künstlers Hendrik Beikirch.
 
Das künstlerische Werk von Hendrik Beikirch (*1974) ist geprägt von intimen Begegnungen mit Menschen. Die ausschließlich aus schwarz-weißen Porträtbildern bestehende Arbeit des deutschen Künstlers bildet einen markanten malerischen Gegenpol zur aktuellen, verzerrenden und ästhetisierenden Medienwelt. Durch die bewusste Wahl der Monochromie, seine unverwechselbare Maltechnik und den eingefangenen Blick seiner Porträtierten schafft Beikirch keine reine Abbildung, sondern drückt ein Gefühl aus, das das Bild durchdringt und zeitgenössische Sehgewohnheiten durchbricht.

Caption: Good Friday - l never quite got the meaning of the “good”.... In Danish, we call this day Langfredag - loosely translating into the MUCH more appropriate “long Friday”. In French we say Vendredi Saint. I am partial to that name for this day - the holiest of days- during Easter. Taking it back to yesterday’s triptych- if you make a 180* in the Santa Maria delle Grazie chapel with your back to Leonardo’s Last Supper masterpiece, you will find this mural artwork on the opposite side. It depicts the crucifixion of Christ and was painted by Giovanni Donato da Montorfano in 1495. Quite the chapel they have going there in Milan! Caption:
LIGHTBRINGER
53m x 6m mural in Holešovice, Prague

It was kind of symbolic to paint the theme of hope in spring time. During those two days of painting I hoped a lot - hoped the storm don't blow me down from ladder, hoped the constant rain and snow won't wash away the paint, I hoped I have enough paint... 
Now I hope that this mural can make at least someone happy

Thank’s @artwise.cz for opportunity, @oklima20 aka @mafietuns for enormous material support 🙏⚪️, @ja.matousek and @razl.lukas.lr for helping me to paint this beast 💪,
@trafo_gallery for lending me the ladder🪜

Caption:
Tonight @9pm EST we sit down with contemporary artist and designer @Marlobro to learn how he's moving through creativity during a time of uncertainty. 
.
Marlo known professionally as MARLOBRO, is an American Contemporary Artist and designer. Who got his start by working with his cousin and founder of Detroit VS Everybody by Tommey Walker and linking up with members of Finally Famous which ultimatly lead to working on mixtape artworks and branding for  Big Sean's early indie career. 
.
He began as a graffiti artist, moving on to studying industrial design at WSU (Wayne state university), and now makes acrylic paintings on canvas and large scale mural paintings. He also collaborates commercially, predominantly on promotional materials, and also clothing, music production and other forms of branding. 
.
His work is exhibited in galleries, outdoors in local and international environments, you can find his work displayed on 1XRUN, PLAYGROUND DETROIT, MURALS IN THE MARKET and avidly collected by individuals. He lives and works in Detroit, Michigan.
.
.
.
.
.

#iaccidentallyfoundoutthat Houston has an underground pedestrian tunnel system. 

The tunnel is 20 feet underground and runs seven miles, linking 95 city blocks.  The tunnel originally connected two cinemas in the city center, but now connects major city buildings, restaurants and retail stores. 

Хьюстон – самый крупный город штата Техас и четвертый по численности населения город в США. 

Хьюстон - промышленный и транспортный центр Техаса.
Нефтяная и газовая промышленность, один из крупнейших портов в мире, крупнейший в мире Техасский медицинский центр и, конечно же, знаменитый центр управления полетами NASA и космический центр - все здесь. 🚀🧑‍🚀

А мурал нарисован Марио Фигероа-младшим, @gonzo247 
Фреска является результатом инициативы "Houston Is Inspiried", выдвинутой Бюро конференций и бизнеса Большого Хьюстона, чтобы подчеркнуть кулинарную и художественную сцену Хьюстона.

Caption:
Jolie découverte de la superbe Exposition à ciel ouvert, afin de rendre l'Art accessible à tous. 
Avec la fermeture des Musées depuis plus d'un an à cause de la crise sanitaire et de la Covid-19, le Projet Murséum a été imaginé et concrétisé à l'initiative de l'Artiste Street Art Masha, afin de faire découvrir des magnifiques Œuvres Street Art, réalisées par plusieurs Street Artistes Talentueux, sur les murs à découvrir dans la ville de Lyon @mashamagosia 
Superbe Illustration et beau collage original au dessus d'un digicode, représentant un joli Poignard dessiné en noir et blanc. 
Magnifique Œuvre Street Art et jolie création artistique originale, réalisée par l'Artiste Zalex Dode à Lyon @boun.ka

Se sitúa en la cabecera sur del parque y dada su posición, actúa como remate visual del mar de colores, efecto realizado por el mosaico Homenaje a la Mujer del Mundo de Byron Gálvez Avilés.

Caption:
Have you checked out our murals yet? Visit link in bio > projects for an insight into our artists works (best viewed on desktop). 

Here is August Sorrow by artist Stelios Kallinikou. 

@stelioskallinikou presents works from his ongoing exploration of the area around Akrotiri, a British overseas territory with a military base in Cyprus, which coincides with a unique biosphere landscape of supra-regional importance as it is the military base for observing developments in the Middle East. 

Radar station focuses both on the RAF (Royal Air Force) Troodos station, one of the main British overseas military installations—in the Troodos mountains since 1878, and on the Starbrook wide-field telescope of the BNSC (British National Space Centre), situated on the same spot since 2016. 
These images are juxtaposed with new works produced during a one-month residency in the Algarve region of southern Portugal, where the trade of enslaved African people took root in Europe.

August sorrow presents speculative scenarios, through which the intersections between territorial and ideological notions relating to 'landscape' - such as space / place and time / history - are explored.

August sorrow was created during a joint artist residency between February - March 2020 at the LAC studios with Akeelah Bertram (UK), Anna Carreras (Spain) and Stelios Kallinikou (Cyprus). LAC, a partner on the CONTESTED DESIRES programme, is based in Lagos, a town in the Algarve region of southern Portugal. The residency followed and responded to ‘Heritage vs. Culture’, the first capacity building workshop of the CONTESTED DESIRES programme that reflected on the colonial legacies of Lagos and how we, as artists, activists and citizens engage with the past that has created the world in which we live.

The digital programme was curated by Dominic Smith.

Caption:
Les comparto el video del proyecto en el que estuve hace  unos días, pintando en la playita. 

La historia de “El Morro”(nombre del gatito) forma parte de una familia que les recuerda el amor y compañía que se tenían el y la persona que se nos adelantó de este plano. 

Me siento muy emocionado cuando pintó historias de familias, anécdotas y ese amor que fluye en sus corazones. 

Abrazamos la vida y honremos la muerte. 

Gracias por seguir confiandome sus historias para plasmarlos en muros, gracias por valorar mi trabajo.

Caption:
Ruth Bader Ginsberg (15 March 1933 - 18 September 2020) New York City, USA.

Justice Ginsberg was a history-making jurist on the US Supreme Court, a feminist icon and American national treasure.

Ginsburg became only the second woman ever to serve as a justice on the nation's highest court. On and off the court, she was a lifelong advocate of gender equality, fond of joking that there would be enough women on the nine-seat Supreme Court "when there are nine".

The 7-foot-tall, 650-pound statue was unveiled last week at City Point Brooklyn, a mixed-use development about a half mile away from the Brooklyn Bridge.

It was created by Australian artists Gillie and Marc, who got Ginsburg's approval for the statue before she died in September 2020 from complications of metastatic pancreas cancer.

Courtesy of @statues.for.equality

Caption:
Crédit photo : @magalimaricot 

Covid : le street art à la rue (lien en bio)

Entre confinement, fermeture des musées et restriction de l'espace public, graffeurs et autres artistes urbains se retrouvent, depuis 1 an, privés de leur espace de création habituel. Quelles alternatives ont-ils trouvé pour continuer à faire passer leurs messages ? La crise sanitaire peut-elle agir comme une catharsis ?

Aujourd'hui, vendredi 2 avril, nous recevons Cécile Denisot pour son article "le street art à l'épreuve de la restriction d'accès à l'espace public" paru sur @letypefr

Caption:
倪匡 // 「喜歡怎麼過日子，可以憑借自己的意思。同樣美麗。」

「音樂是沒有高低級之分，有一些人推崇古典音樂，不知是基於什麼樣的滑稽心態。今日稱之為古典音樂者，昔年也一樣是流行音樂；今日之流行音樂，若干年之後，也就成了古典音樂。」

「你愛看的書，就是你該看的書。書海浩瀚，總有你愛看的，那就看。不愛看的，別浪費生命。若看了古文就惹氣，那就看今文。看書的主要目的，是在看的過程得到快樂，享受閱讀帶來的樂趣，那樂趣是越看越濃的。十年業余讀古文，所得閱讀樂趣之多，肯定非同小可。」

「古語叫『授人以柄』，即把劍給別人刺自己，好不智。」

Ni Kuang, is a Hong Kong-American novelist and screenwriter. He has written over 300 Chinese-language wuxia and science fiction novels, and more than 400 film scripts.

イースター工作その3、塗り絵。
工作じゃないけど壁画アーティストのミヤザキケンスケさんの塗り絵。

娘の塗り絵を見てハッと気付かされたのは、肌の色が一色ではないところ。ブラウン、オレンジ、白…と当然のように使う娘。

.

昨年のイースター当日。
軽い気持ちでこの塗り絵をしてから散歩に出掛けよう！なんて思ってたら。意外な几帳面さ(?)を発揮して、上半分を完成させるのに気付いたらお昼。

お花も塗ると言うので夜に持ち越し、人も塗ってないと言うので翌日に持ち越し、細かいとろが終わってないと言うので追加し…。と、まさかの3日😲

2枚目→娘
3枚目→私

私も一緒に塗ってみました。
ミトンの下は芝桜。途中で娘はちょいちょい私の真似をし出したから、離れたところに避難しました😅

.

4/15/2020

Caption:
[Sách ảnh - bìa cứng - tiếng Anh]

Bộ sưu tập ảnh được xuất bản đầu tiên của biểu tượng phong cách đường phố, tập hợp các bức ảnh được đăng trên The New York Times cùng với các tác phẩm chưa từng thấy trong suốt 5 thập kỷ.

Nhiếp ảnh của Bill Cunningham đã ghi lại sự phát triển của phong cách, xu hướng và cuộc sống hàng ngày, cả ở Thành phố New York và ở Paris. Nhưng tác phẩm của ông cũng cho thấy phong cách đường phố không chỉ có thời trang; đó là về con người và sự thay đổi văn hóa.
 
Từ thập kỷ này sang thập kỷ khác, bắt đầu từ những năm 1970 và tiếp tục cho đến khi Cunningham qua đời vào năm 2016. Tại đây, bạn sẽ tìm thấy biên niên sử đặc biệt của Cunningham về  những năm 1980 đình công, sự trỗi dậy của những ngày thứ sáu bình thường của thập niên 1990, nỗi buồn ập xuống thành phố sau ngày 11/9, sự xuất hiện của ảnh tự chụp và nhiều khoảnh khắc quan trọng khác.
 
Các bài luận cung cấp bức chân dung tiết lộ về Cunningham và một vài trong số những niềm đam mê và ảnh hưởng của ông ấy, được đóng góp bởi Cathy Horyn, Tiina Loite, Vanessa Friedman, Ruth La Ferla, Guy Trebay, Penelope Green, Jacob Bernstein, và một người rất được yêu thích, Anna Wintour. 
 
“Một chiếc kính vạn hoa chói lọi từ cái nhìn của một nghệ sĩ, người luôn nhìn thấy vẻ đẹp ở mọi góc độ.” - André Leon Talley

Caption:
"L'éther nu"
Caligraffiti: "Dans l'air - Chanson des oiseaux" de Victor Hugo

Acrylique sur bois flotté

"Vie ! ô bonheur ! bois profonds,
Nous vivons.
L’essor sans fin nous réclame ;
Planons sur l’air et les eaux !
Les oiseaux
Sont de la poussière d’âme.

Accourez, planez ! volons
Aux vallons,
A l’antre, à l’arbre, à l’asile !
Perdons-nous dans cette mer
De l’éther
Où la nuée est une île !"

Caption:
Paseando por las bellas callecitas de Palermo (Buenos Aires) me encontré con este mural, pequeño, no estaba en ningún local, en una pared al lado de un taller mecánico, me gustó su frescura, la relación entre esa niña y ese 🐶, tuve que retratarlo y automáticamente More se puso para ser fotografiada también; ese instante donde la gente no transita por el medio de la foto, donde se disparo mi camara-celular y de pronto...sale un señor desde adentro del taller diciéndole a More que salga tan hermosa como esa nena retratada allí en ese mural, quien es su nieta. 
Como me encantan las historias y el por qué de de mural , le pregunté cómo había sido y me contó la historia: @pintaargentinaok pinto a su nieta a partir de una foto que él le dio junto al perrito y para el es una forma de recordarla cuando no puede verla tan seguido.

Continuamos la caminata donde seguí sacando fotos las cuales iré subiendo a las historías.

🌈 Buen jueves y no dejen de observar detenidamente lo que nos rodea, el arte nos envuelve y está presente a cada paso.

Caption:
🎨 Arnaldo Moura
Comecei a me envolver mais com a pintura há mais ou menos uns 7 anos, sempre aliei meu trabalho artístico com o fazer Teatral.
⠀
Atualmente fazendo parte de um grupo de Teatro chamado Garajal, e por conta desse grupo comecei a desenvolver trabalhos manuais e me identifiquei muito com a pintura. Desenvolvendo técnicas com tinta acrílica, mas sem nem uma escola de pintura definida. Aprendi muito vendo tutoriais, com a prática e a observação. Ao longo do tempo me dedico muito a aperfeiçoar mais minhas habilidades descobrindo formas e traços.
⠀
Acho que o que pinto pelo menos até o presente momento, é a motivação de comunicar o que de alguma forma passa ou passou pela minha experiência enquanto ser humano. E é a figura humana que me atrai, essa pluralidade cultural, de diversidade e diferenças, então o humano nas suas diversas formas e cores possa ser o caminho para a resposta do porquê.
⠀
Entendo que vivo em um tempo de mundo onde existi um fluxo dinâmico da contemporaneidade, as artes sempre se reinventando, e busco em muitas vezes quando desenvolvo algum trabalho uma integração entre as artes plásticas, música e artes cênica para de alguma forma traduzir essa motivação de comunicar.
.

Caption:
안녕하세요.
로로아트플랜입니다. ^^
 
 
이번에 소개해드릴 작품은
벽면의 미관을 개선하고
포토스팟으로서의 효과를 목적으로
 
여수 라마다 호텔에서 진행한
벽화 작품들입니다.

드넓은 바다와 화창한 하늘의 푸른 색감과
바닷속을 자유롭게 유영하는 거대한 범고래를 표현한 벽화,
 
해질녘 아름다운 노을을 좌측면에 표현하고
돌산대교와 아름다운 야경들을 표현한 벽화,

넓고 푸른 바다와 파도가 밀려드는 백사장을
재미있는 공간감으로 구성하여 미관을 개선한 벽화,

바닷속에 뛰어드는 사람의 모습과
마찰로 인해 발생한 물보라를 다이나믹하게 표현한 벽화,
 
바닷속을 잠수중인 잠수부와
해양생물들이 표현된 벽화,
 
범고래, 돌고래, 거북이와 시원한 바닷물을
생동감 있게 표현한 벽화,
 
기존의 평범한 출입구의 미관을 개선하여
마치 에메랄드빛 바다의 휴양지로 떠나는 컨셉의 벽화 등을

방문객들로 하여금 기억에 남는 포토스팟의
역할을 할 수 있도록 진행하였습니다.
 
여수 라마다 호텔에서 진행한
벽화 작품들이였습니다.

Caption:
Aloha everyone! This week, we're featuring a small town from Kauai, the northernmost island in Hawaii. This wall honors Hanapepe, "Kauai's Biggest Little Town."⁠
.⁠
Known as the art capital of the island, Hanapepe is a small community that boasts a lot of creative talent in its population of just under 3,000 locals. Learn all about this community and some of the traditions that inspired this design in the full blog post at smalltownwalls.com (link in bio!)⁠
.⁠
For this town especially, I am SO grateful for the information made available by local native Hawaiian artisans, historians, and journalists. Mahalo to @aloha.authentic, Ho’okulena LLC,  and @hanahoumag for the informative content you share. As always, all resources are linked at the bottom of the full post for further exploration 😎⁠
.⁠

Caption:
BUENOS AIRES 🇦🇷 
ESPECIAL DIEGO Y #LASMALVINAS PARTE 2 
Mural realizado en la unidad penitenciaria N°43 de González Catán, donde el grupo muralista #MarleyGraffitis rindió homenaje al 10 y a su amor por las #IslasMalvinas.
Una leyenda reza 4-B Solo para entendidos, no sabemos a quienes se refieren ;) 
📒 #114 "EMural en la casa de Pipi"
🖌  @marley_graffitis 
🗓 2021
Nota: @radiomitre
La obra de arte es creación de los propiospresos para mantener viva la memoria del ídolo entre los detenidos. Esto se debe a que muchos de los que están privados de su libertad son jóvenes y solo conocieron al “Diez” en su época como director técnico de Gimnasia y Esgrima La Plata.
La pieza mide 8 metros de largo por 3 de alto y su diseño se hizo realidad gracias al grupo de graffiteros que contribuyó conocido como “Marley Graffitis”. Entre ellos estaban Maximiliano Jaldín, Víctor Sánchez y Roberto Llanes, quienes contribuyeron con su conocimiento y técnica al retrato.

Caption:
As you guys know, it’s crazy, but I’m in MexIco now. Why? Well not for the grill parties and tequila really. I am looking forward to the inspirational boost for my coming abstract series 🌟 and a few art collabs in the way 😄
I really like murals and the effect of a painted wall: cracks, texture all that jazz, as soon as I get my hands on some canvas over here, I will start my experiments and I’m excited to see how it’s gonna turn out 😄
This one magically appeared from behind the corner when I was on my discovery stroll through the city  and I just loved the mood 😄🌟 
Is it something you would guys recommend when it comes to Cancún? Places, venues, inspirations?
